The '''Sith battle suit''' was a remarkably flexible medium [[combat suit]] that was manufactured by [[Aratech Repulsor Company/Legends|Aratech Repulsor Company]] in the wake of the [[Jedi Civil War]]. The name was inspired, not developed, by the actual [[Darth Revan's Sith Empire|Sith Empire]]; Aratech hoped to profit from the organization's fame. This type of [[Armor/Legends|armor]] was white and black in appearance and provided a significant amount of protection while retaining a rather high level of flexibility when compared to other armors of that weight class.

[[Meetra Surik]], or members of her party, may have acquired and utilized Sith battle suits during the [[First Jedi Purge]].

